txt.en: 'Here are the hides that you gathered -- and now they should go to their proper home: the Rohirrim from Stangard. They have made camp at the bottom of the wood along the river before they make the remainder of their journey home.\n\n'You should bring them this gift from the Elves before they depart for good, for this will be our last chance to make contact with the trespassers.'
'Hail, [placeholder]. Thank you for this gift... but tell me: is this from Noriel? How does she fare? What can you tell me about her? Do you think she would agree to see me again?'
A Gift of Warmth in Winter
Renfaer has asked you to deliver Noriel's gift for the departing Rohirrim of Stangard.
Bring the gift of hides to Wynmar at his new camp
Wynmar and his men are at their new temporary camp on the southern river-bank of Thinglad.\n\nYou should bring the hides to Wynmar as a final parting gift, a token of good will from the Elves.
